    • Field Detail

      • bandwidth

        @Option
public Double bandwidth
        The bandwidth used to compute the kernel density estimate. By default, the bandwidth is determined by Silverman's rule of thumb.

      • box

        @Option
public final ViolinBoxOptions box
        Determines if an miniature box plot is drawn inside the violins.

      • fillcolor

        @Option
public String fillcolor
        The fill color.

        Default: A half-transparent variant of the line color, marker color, or marker line color, whichever is available.

      • hoveron

        @Option
public String hoveron
        Any combination of "violins", "points", "kde" joined with a "+" OR "all". examples: "violins", "points", "violins+points", "violins+points+kde", "all" default: "violins+points+kde"

      • jitter

        @Option
public Double jitter
        The amount of jitter in the sample points drawn. If "0", the sample points align along the distribution axis. If "1", the sample points are drawn in a random jitter of width equal to the width of the violins.

        Constraints: ≥0 and ≤1

      • line_color

        @Option(value="line.color")
public String line_color
        The color of line bounding the violin(s).

      • line_width

        @Option(value="line.width")
public Integer line_width
        The width (in px) of line bounding the violin(s).

        Default: 2

      • marker

        @Option
public final MarkerOptions marker
        Options for marker.

      • meanline_color

        @Option(value="meanline.color")
public String meanline_color
        The mean line color.

      • meanline_visible

        @Option(value="meanline.visible")
public Boolean meanline_visible
        Determines if a line corresponding to the sample's mean is shown inside the violins. If "box.visible" is turned on, the mean line is drawn inside the inner box. Otherwise, the mean line is drawn from one side of the violin to other.

      • meanline_width

        @Option(value="meanline.width")
public Integer meanline_width
        The mean line width.

      • orientation

        @Option
public VHOrientationEnum orientation
        The orientation of the violin(s).

      • pointpos

        @Option
public Integer pointpos
        The position of the sample points in relation to the violins. If "0", the sample points are placed over the center of the violins. Positive/negative values correspond to positions to the right/left for vertical violins and above/below for horizontal violins.

      • points

        @Option
public PointsFilterEnum points
        Determines which points are displayed.

      • scalegroup

        @Option
public String scalegroup
        If there are multiple violins that should be sized according to to some metric (see "scalemode"), link them by providing a non-empty group id here shared by every trace in the same group.

      • scalemode

        @Option
public PlotViolin.ScaleModeEnum scalemode
        The metric by which the width of each violin is determined.

        Default: WIDTH

      • selected

        @Option
public final SelectedOptions selected

      • side

        @Option
public PlotViolin.SideEnum side
        Determines on which side of the position value the density function making up one half of a violin is plotted. Useful when comparing two violin traces under "overlay" mode, where one trace has "side" set to "positive" and the other to "negative".

      • span

        @Option
public double[] span
        The span in data space for which the density function will be computed. Has an effect only when "spanmode" is set to MANUAL.

      • spanmode

        @Option
public PlotViolin.SpanModeEnum spanmode
        The method by which the span in data space where the density function will be computed.

        Default: SOFT

      • text$array

        @Option(value="text")
public String[] text$array
        The text elements associated with each sample value as an array of string where the items are mapped in order to the this trace's (x,y) coordinates. To be seen, trace "hoverinfo" must contain a "text" flag.

      • text$string

        @Option(value="text")
public String text$string
        The text elements associated with each sample value as a single string where the same string appears over all the data points. To be seen, trace "hoverinfo" must contain a "text" flag.

      • unselected

        @Option
public final SelectedOptions unselected

      • x

        @Option
public double[] x
        The x sample data or coordinates.

      • x0$number

        @Option(value="x0")
public Double x0$number
        The x coordinate of the box.

      • x0$string

        @Option(value="x0")
public String x0$string
        The x coordinate of the box as a categorical string.

      • xaxis

        @Option
public String xaxis
        Reference between this trace's x coordinates and a 2D Cartesian x axis. If "x" (the default value), the x coordinates refer to "layout.xaxis". If "x2", the x coordinates refer to "layout.xaxis2", and so on.

      • y

        @Option
public double[] y
        The y sample data or coordinates.

      • y0$number

        @Option(value="y0")
public Double y0$number
        The y coordinate of the box.

      • y0$string

        @Option(value="y0")
public String y0$string
        The y coordinate of the box as a categorical string.

      • yaxis

        @Option
public String yaxis
        Reference between this trace's y coordinates and a 2D Cartesian y axis. If "y" (the default value), the y coordinates refer to "layout.yaxis". If "y2", the y coordinates refer to "layout.xaxis2", and so on.
